    <figure id="id14677864">
      <media id="id14677864_media" alt="">
        <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics2-6a32.png" id="id14677864__onlineimage" height="42" width="63"/>
      </media>
    </figure>
    <para id="id14466389">This is called Diode amplitude stabilization of a Wien Bridge Oscillator.</para>
    <para id="id13244851">Determine frequency of oscillation &amp; the amplitude of the oscillation.</para>
    <para id="id13244855">[Ans:- 9.95 kHz,3.0V]</para>
    <para id="id13244860">When the diodes are off,the gain of the amplifier is <figure id="id14444697"><media id="id14444697_media" alt=""><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics3-b8d5.png" id="id14444697__onlineimage" height="35" width="208"/></media></figure></para>
    <para id="id14565426">So that loop gain &gt;1 and the oscillations grow.</para>
    <para id="id14565433">When diode turn ON, the gain is <figure id="id14510629"><media id="id14510629_media" alt=""><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics4-8c37.png" id="id14510629__onlineimage" height="35" width="267"/></media></figure>and the oscillations decay.</para>
    <para id="id14452041">PROBLEM(2)</para>
